nodes.label: message
nodes.text: Atypical means that cells are not normal but not completely abnormal either - the way Dr Person1 explained it,  there is a spectrum of cells where typical and atypical cells are - so atypical cells can be anywhere on that spectrum past typical. Best thing to do is follow up with ENT, which you are doing. They will keep a clo se eye on it and monitor for changes. Unclear right now to know exactly what it is since the path didn't state cancer directly. Dr Person1 wants you to know that you are doing great! I will keep an eye out for the CT neck results and have Dr Person1 review.
